On 4/28/2011 10:20 AM, kahuna wrote:
> i had the same thing happen a few years ago in my 78, the lock cylinder had imploded.  i had to swipe my own bus.  luckily i had already taken it apart once so i had cross cut those anti theft bolts, otherwise i would have been screwed.  a long time ago, when i knew a lot less than i do now, my vanagon quit in FLA. i called a tow truck on a friday and asked if he knew of a vw repair guy.  he took me out to this crazy place littered with old vw's. the guy could not have been nicer.  in 1 minute of diagnosis he said 'switch is fubar, $20 for a used one installed" sweet, i was back on the road in 10 minutes!
>
> moral of the story is carry an extra switch, the electric part.....you don't really need the key part to be working.
>
> kahuna
